<HEAD>Former UAW President Douglas Fraser Endorses Dukakis</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Massachusetts Gov. Michael Dukakis has picked up
an endorsement from a top labor figure.
   Douglas Fraser, former president of the United Auto Workers
union, said Sunday in his announcement that Dukakis is the
Democrats' best hope for winning the November election.
   Dukakis, who was taking the day off from campaigning, said the
endorsement will give him momentum heading into the Michigan
Democratic caucuses March 26.
   ``His (Fraser's) endorsement will give a tremendous boost to my
campaign. I think it shows that our campaign is truly a national
campaign,'' Dukakis said.
   On Saturday, Dukakis, the Rev. Jesse Jackson and U.S. Rep.
Richard Gephardt made stops in Michigan, meeting with plant
workers, chatting with the chairman of the party's Platform
Committee, taking a train ride and raising some money.
