<HEAD>French Jumbo Lands at Arctic Base after Bomb Threat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Air France jumbo jet made an
unscheduled landing at the U.S. air base at Thule in northern
Greenland because of a bomb threat, Greenland's military command
said today.
   The Boeing 747 en route to Tokyo landed at Thule late Sunday
night after the Paris headquarters of the French national carrier
received an anonymous telephone threat saying there was a bomb on
board.
   The 396 passengers were evacuated without incident and given
shelter in the base's movie theater.
   After a four-hour search of the airliner and all the baggage, it
was allowed to resume its flight via Anchorage, Alaska.
