<HEAD>Cyclone Death Toll Rises To 100</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAPUTO, Mozambique (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The death toll from a cyclone earlier
this month in Mozambique has risen to 100, the national news agency
AIM reported today.
   Cyclone Filao struck March 1 and damaged large parts of the port
city of Quelimane and surrounding rural areas in Zambezia province.
   The news agency last week reported the cyclone had killed 57
people. It said today the toll rose as more information was
received from remote areas.
   The cyclone destroyed 1,000 homes, leaving an estimated 4,500
people homeless, AIM said.
