<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--WindshieldAssault     03-14 0171</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Windshield Assault,0175</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Windshield-Washer Attacked with Bat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A windshield-washer was in critical condition
today after a motorist who did not want his windshield washed
cracked the man over the head with a baseball bat.
   Police spokesman Sgt. Maurice Howard said 47-year-old Eldred
Leitzse of the Bronx started to wash the windshield on a light
green Mercedes stopped at the light at about 7 p.m. last night.
   The driver of the car, one of three men in the car, apparently
did not ask for the wash and did not want it, Howard said. He
stepped from the car and hit Leitzse over the head with a bat,
Howard says.
   Windshield-washers in New York often are poor people who
approach cars at stoplights and offer to wash their windows for a
small tip. Occasionally the washers refuse to stop unless paid.
   Harlem Hospital administrator Edward Titus said Leitzse was in
critical but stable condition this morning.
   No one has been arrested and no other details were immediately
available.
</TEXT>
