<HEAD>Three Saudi Diplomats Wounded</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A masked man shot and wounded three Saudi
Arabian diplomats in an ambush in the parking lot of Lagos hotel, a
newspaper said.
   A fourth diplomat escaped injury and pursued the gunman, the
government-owned New Nigerian reported. It said the assailant
escaped over a nearby wall.
   The four Saudis were fired upon as they left the Eko Holiday Inn
in a car at 2 a.m. Sunday, the newspaper said. It said the gunmen
apparently had been waiting for them.
   Two of the wounded diplomats were in serious condition, while
the third suffered a less severe wound, the newspaper said. Their
names were not made public.
   Both police and the Saudi Embassy refused to answer questions
about the incident.
   The New Nigerian quoted police sources who said witnesses
described the gunman as an Arab.
   There was no immediate claim of responsibility for the shootings.
   A Libyan diplomat was shot and killed in Lagos in January.
Police said the diplomat was slain by robbers who were caught.
Government and police sources said they could not rule out the
possibility that the Libyan had been killed by Chadians.
