<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--Brink'sRobbery     03-14 0167</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Brink's Robbery,0171</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Brink's Warehouse Robbed of 25 Cash Boxes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five thieves broke into a Brink's warehouse and
stole 25 cash boxes collected from a supermarket chain's automatic
tellers, police said Monday.
   The robbery Sunday was partly filmed by a surveillance camera,
but the fuzzy image failed to show the burglars' features, said
police Sgt. David Rivero. Technical experts were trying to enhance
the film.
   The boxes had been collected Saturday night, and because they
had been used all day it was doubtful there was much cash in each
box, he said.
   Police and Brink's of Florida Inc. officials were going through
teller records to determine how much money was taken. When full,
the boxes would have held an average of about $10,000.
   The camera showed five men breaking in the outside door of the
warehouse early Sunday. They made their way directly to the boxes,
Rivero said.
   The robbery was discovered when Brink's employees showed up for
work Sunday morning, he said.
</TEXT>
