<HEAD>Brink's Guards Beat Back Robbers near Rome</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Guards in a Brink's armored truck foiled a robbery
attempt Monday when they returned fire on armed bandits who blocked
a street on the city's outskirts with a truck and road grader,
police said.
   Five or six bandits opened fire on the armored truck from behind
the roadblock and from a car, police said. But the guards shot back
and forced the bandits to flee.
   There were no reports of injuries to guards or robbers.
   Authorities did not disclose how much money was aboard the
Brink's Securmark truck that was carrying the payroll for five or
six businesses.
