<HEAD>Pentagon Proposes Sale of Torpedoes to Canada</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Pentagon notified Congress on Monday it
had approved the sale of MK-48 torpedoes to Canada.
   Assuming there are no congressional objections, Canada will be
offered 13 of the torpedoes for roughly $16 million, the Pentagon
said.
   The Ocean Systems Division of Gould Inc. in Euclid, Ohio, will
serve as the prime contractor and the U.S. Navy will be responsible
for overseeing the transaction, the Pentagon added.
   ``The government of Canada needs these torpedoes for its
Oberon-class submarines,'' the Pentagon said. ``These torpedoes can
also be used on replacement submarines planned ... for the 1990s.''
