<HEAD>Lightning Knocks Out Two Engines, Plane Lands Safely</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lightning struck the fuselage of a passenger jet
over the Ukraine, knocking out two of the three engines, but the
pilot landed the plane safely, the government newspaper Izvestia
reported Monday.
   It said the Tupolev 154, on a flight from Taskhkent to Donetsk
in the southern Ukraine, was hit by lightning Sunday about nine
miles from Donetsk.
   One engine died and the second stalled but the pilot, identified
as S. Kharkov, showed ``presence of mind and high skill'' in
landing the aircraft at the Donetsk airport, the paper said.
   Izvestia did not say how many people were on the plane, which
can carry about 160 passengers, and did not mention injuries.
