<HEAD>Bulgaria Establishes Duty Free Zones, Report Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bulgaria has established two duty free
zones to ``encourage economic cooperaton'' between Bulgarian and
foreign companies, the state-run BTA news agency reported Monday.
   BTA said the zones were set up in the cities of Rousse and
Vidin, and offered areas where ``economic activities can be carried
out ... without duties or taxes.''
   The report did not say when the duty free zones were
established, or provide further details.
</TEXT>
