<HEAD>Wickes Unit, Shiroki in Auto-Parts Joint Venture</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA MONICA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A unit of Wickes Cos. Inc. said
Monday it has formed a joint venture with Shiroki Corp. of
Yokohama, Japan, to design and manufacture window regulators for
the North American auto market.
   The Wickes unit, Wickes Manufacturing Co. of Southfield, Mich.,
and Shiroki currently are leading suppliers of components to
automakers in the United States and Japan.
   Window regulators control the speed and position of power
windows, which Wickes said are expected to dominate an increasingly
large share of the U.S. market.
   Wickes Manufacturing makes a variety of electroninc and
mechanical auto components and last fiscal year sold about $1
billion in original equipment to automakers. It also sells smaller
amounts of auto parts in the secondary market.
